    public abstract class ExecutionTimeBasedTimeout
extends Object
implements Timeout
    Abstract class for timeouts deciding when to stop based on the executed programâ€™s run time. Subclasses should always call super.init() when overriding init(). They are also encouraged to check on the initialised flag in all methods.The class furthermore provides functionality to register and unregister callbacks.
